OL,6,FPart of the #3 million funding will
OL,7,Falso be spent on developing
OL,8,F"diversionary programmes" aimed at
OL,9,Freducing reoffending and youth
OL,10,Foffending.
OL,12,FMr Mairs continued: "We know that
OL,13,Fenforcement alone cannot successfully
OL,14,Freduce retail crime and so the
OL,15,Fpartnership approach to safeguarding
OL,16,Fstores and exploring opportunities to
OL,17,Fwork collaboratively to address the
OL,18,Froot causes of such offences will play
OL,19,Fa significant role in the work of the
OL,20,Ftaskforce.
